    "description": "The base principle is simple you search a house looking for things that were different in the original (anomalies). In case you find such an anomaly, you report it by pressing a button, and afterwards you loop back into a new iteration of the house. When you report right 13 times, you win.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe games random nature leads to ever different runs.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThere are 30 anomalies that might appear in the rooms. However, there may only be a maximum of one anomaly at one time. As such, the playthrough length may differ drastically from ca. 40-80 minutes for the first playthrough.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you dare to enter the dark rooms of Monday the 14th, be assured that while you challenge your memory and luck, you will be observed.",
